'''''Tuya's Marriage''''' ([[Chinese language|Chinese]]: <U+5716><U+96C5><U+7684><U+5A5A><U+4E8B>; Tuya de hun shi) is a [[2007]] [[Chinese film]] directed by [[Quanan Wang]]. The film depicts life in [[Inner Mongolia]], in a region where [[desertification]] is making life hard for farmers. It tells the story of Tuya, who divorces her disabled husband in the hope of finding an able-bodied husband who will be prepared to look after both herself and her former husband.

The film won the [[Golden Bear]] at the [[Berlin Film Festival]].

